1 Section 1. Section 81-836, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 81-836 (1) It shall be the policy of the State of Nebraska to:
4 (a) Support the civilian and military command of the United States
5 and its efforts to promote and maintain prosperity, peace, and security
6 for America and its allies;
7 (b) Enhance the defensive posture of this state so as to protect
8 state citizens and assets and to contribute to the broader defensive
9 posture of the United States by reducing security vulnerabilities within
10 this state; and
11 (c) Exercise foresight and make reasonable preparations for a
12 potential regional or global conflict centered on the Pacific theater
13 which could involve attacks upon the United States and its allies in the
14 Pacific theater, which could involve asymmetrical attacks on the American
15 homeland, and which could cause the disruption or complete severing of
16 supply chains between this state and its vendors and the People's
17 Republic of China, the Republic of China, or other countries in the
18 Pacific theater.
19 (2) The Committee on Pacific Conflict is hereby created. The
20 committee shall consist of the following seven voting members:
21 (a) The Director of State Homeland Security, appointed pursuant to
22 section 81-830, who shall serve as chairperson of the committee;
23 (b) The Director of Administrative Services;
24 (c) The state investment officer;
25 (d) The Adjutant General; and
26 (e) Three individuals with applicable knowledge of the threats posed
27 to this state in the event of a Pacific conflict, including at least one
28 individual who represents an entity that is responsible for the operation
29 and maintenance of critical infrastructure in this state. Such
30 individuals shall be appointed by the Governor.
31 (3) The committee shall also include five four members of the
-2-

