1 Legislature, to be appointed by the Executive Board of the Legislative
2 Council. The legislative members shall be nonvoting members of the
3 committee.
4 (4) Appointments to the committee shall be made within sixty days
5 after April 17, 2024.
6 (4) (5) The committee shall be authorized for an initial period of
7 three years.
8 (5) (6) The first meeting of the committee shall be held within
9 ninety days after April 17, 2024.
10 (6) (7) The committee shall meet no less than once every three
11 months. Additional meetings may be called at the will of the majority of
12 the voting members of the committee, and emergency meetings may be called
13 at the will of the chairperson of the committee or the Governor. In the
14 interest of state and national security, meetings of the committee shall
15 not be subject to the Open Meetings Act and the records and documents of
16 the committee shall not be considered public records for purposes of
17 sections 84-712 to 84-712.09.
18 (7) (8) At the discretion of the committee, an advisory board may be
19 established and subject matter experts may be consulted to provide
20 expertise or collaborative research support.
21 (8) (9) The committee is authorized to liaise with relevant federal
22 government authorities, authorities from other state governments, and
23 experts from research institutions for the purpose of obtaining
24 information that is useful for the committee's work.
25 (9) (10) The committee is authorized to produce policy
26 recommendations for the State of Nebraska.
27 (10) (11) The committee is authorized to conduct secure hearings or
28 briefings with critical infrastructure providers for the purpose of
29 understanding the threats, risks, and vulnerabilities posed to critical
30 infrastructure in the event of a Pacific conflict, including potential
31 mitigation or emergency response strategies.
