1 (11) (12) The Governor shall annually produce and publish a state
2 threat assessment no later than the day prior to the annual address made
3 to the Legislature by the Governor. The annual state threat assessment
4 shall provide an overview of the substantial threats to state or national
5 security, state or national economic security, state or national public
6 health, or any combination of such matters, occurring within and
7 threatening the State of Nebraska to the extent such information can be
8 provided and stored in a manner that meets national security standards.
9 The state threat assessment shall include summary nonconfidential
10 findings of the Committee on the Pacific Conflict. Such summary
11 nonconfidential findings shall include no information that would create
12 any risk to state critical infrastructure or other sensitive state
13 assets.
14 (12) (13) The committee may, at the discretion of the committee and
15 upon an affirmative vote of five of the committee's seven voting members,
16 produce a confidential report that shall be kept in a secure location to
17 be determined by the Governor and which shall only be accessed with the
18 approval of the Governor. Such report shall contain information,
19 instructions, and other findings that the committee deems useful to
20 preserve for the elected leaders of the State of Nebraska.
21 Sec. 2. Original section 81-836, Reissue Revised Statutes of
22 Nebraska, is repealed.
